--- SCENARIO: in a herson draft only the host may ban, and host bans are honored ---
# Herson has no per-player ban phase. A non-host /ban is rejected with a clear comment; the host may
# remove civs from the pool at any time before the draft closes, and those show up in the status.

--- CHAT ---
alice: /lobby herson
bob: /register

--- DM (alice) ---
alice: /leaders
ambotorix: <button "{leader}">
--- DM (bob) ---
bob: /leaders
ambotorix: <button "{leader}">

--- CHAT ---
bob: /ban montezuma                # non-host -> rejected (reply lands in bob's DM)
--- DM (bob) ---
ambotorix: Only the host can ban civs in a Herson draft.

--- CHAT ---
alice: /ban montezuma              # host -> banned
--- DM (alice) ---
ambotorix: ✅ Banned*Montezuma*

--- CHAT ---
ambotorix: <status *Draft: herson*Host bans:*Montezuma*>
ambotorix:
